  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies the CICP (Coding-Independent Code Points) transfer function for a color space.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp` enumerates the electro-optical transfer functions (EOTF/OETF) defined by ITU-T H.273 (CICP). The transfer function describes how scene-linear light values are encoded into a signal and decoded back to display light.

Use this enumeration with <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(SkiaSharp.SKColorspacePrimariesCicp,SkiaSharp.SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp)> to create a color space from standard CICP identifiers.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create an HDR PQ (Perceptual Quantizer) color space with Rec. 2020 primaries
var colorSpace = SKColorSpace.CreateCicp(
    SKColorspacePrimariesCicp.Rec2020,
    SKColorspaceTransferFnCicp.Pq);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
